              <h2>Simons Foundation Privacy Policy</h2>
             	<p>Thank you for visiting the Simons Foundation 
				website. The following policy describes how the 
				Simons Foundation collects and uses information from 
				visitors to this site. </p>
				<h3>Registration</h3>
				<p>Researchers are invited to participate in the 
				Simons Foundation scientific community. </p>
				<p>Only registered researchers can submit comments 
				on website articles and for On SFARI (autism blog). 
				If you comment, your user name can be seen by all 
				visitors to those website pages. </p>
				<h3>Use of Information</h3>
				<p>The information collected from you will be used 
				to grant access for comments and to participate in 
				discussions with other registered researchers on the 
				website. We need your email address in order to send 
				you confirmation of your user identity and password.
				</p>
				<p>The Simons Foundation may also track and use 
				aggregate information about visitors for internal 
				purposes, to assess and improve the content of our 
				web pages. From time to time we may ask visitors to 
				respond to inquiries regarding content or web 
				features. </p>
				<p>The information collected from you is not 
				distributed to any third party for any purpose. </p>
				<p>Your registration information is secured by 
				current, reasonable industry standards. You may opt 
				out of SF communications at any time by
				<a href="https://id.sfari.org/i/contact-us">
				contacting us</a>. </p>
